Exception Summary
EmergencyStopException thrown, if an emergency stop condition arises.
EventTimedoutException thrown, if an awaited event, did not occur in time
InconsistencyException thrown, if an internal error has been encountered by the runtime environment of jPac
IndexOutOfRangeException thrown, if an index is out of range, while accessing data of a process image
InEveryCycleDoException thrown to the work() method of a module, if an exception condition has been encountered while processing inEveryCycleDo().
InputInterlockException thrown at a module (inside work()), if the application code implemented inside AbstractModule.preCheckInterlocks() encounters an error condition
InterlockException base class for interlock exceptions
InvalidPropertyException thrown, if an error occurs, while accessing a property
MonitorException thrown at a module (inside work()), if an event (Fireable) has been fired, which is monitored by it
NumberOutOfRangeException thrown, if a value to be assigned to decimal or signed integer exceeds the signals range of values
OutputInterlockException thrown at a module (inside work()), if the application code implemented inside AbstractModule.postCheckInterlocks() encounters an error condition
PinAlreadyAssignedException not approved!
PinIncompatibleException not approved!
PinNotAssignedException not approved!
PlugIncompatibleException not approved!
ProcessException base class of all jPac related exceptions
RemoteSignalException thrown, if a problem with a remote signal arises
ShutdownRequestException is thrown at every module (inside work()), if some instance (another module calling shutdown() or the OS) requests a shutdown of the elbfisch application.
SignalAccessException thrown, if a module tries to set() a signal, which does not belong to it (the module is not the containing module of the signal), or the signal is connected by another signal as a target signal.
SignalAlreadyConnectedException thrown, if a attempt is made to connect a signal as a target more than once
SignalAlreadyExistsException thrown, if a signal with the same name already exists
SignalInvalidException thrown, if an attempt is made to read a signal which is invalid
SignalNotRegisteredException thrown, if an attempt is made to fetch a signal, which is not present (registered) yet
SomeEventsNotProcessedException thrown by jPac, if not all modules could have been processed in time
